Frequently asked questions

Select 'View statements' for an account to see your online statements and older transactions.

You can find out how often and when we pay interest on an account by expanding the 'Interest rate' section on this page. If the interest rate is affected by withdrawals, you'll find that information there too.

If your account has tiered interest rates, we'll highlight the rate that your account is currently receiving. This is based on your account's cleared balance at the end of the previous working day - not the available balance.

We'll notify you in advance if an interest rate is changing. This is explained in our terms and conditions.

An arranged overdraft is a way to borrow money from your current account up to an agreed limit for a short time. Your overdraft limit is displayed under your current account's available balance. Interest charges apply.

Read more about overdrafts 

This is a list of registered holders for an account - the individual account holders for a personal account, or the name of the business for a business account.

Third parties with access to an account or with lasting power of attorney for an account holder aren't shown on this list.

Please contact us if the list of registered holders for an account is wrong.
You can generate the International Bank Account Number (IBAN) for any of your International Bank Account Number accounts using our tool.

If you need a copy of a Statement for a specific period, there are several options for you to choose from:

Online Statements

The statement that you need may already be available to download and print. You can search your statement archive by selecting 'Online Statements' from the drop-down menu under your name on the Online Banking homepage, then select the account you want to see statements for.

Statements and documents

We've uploaded your paper statements and Online Statements from June 2013 onward into your cloud. You can view, print and download these whenever you want. Have a look at Statements and documents
